President Trump signed an executive order addressing the issue of veteran suicide, calling it a "solemn crisis" that requires urgent national action. He expressed his commitment to mobilizing every level of American society to save the lives of veterans and support them in their time of need. The executive order establishes a new Cabinet-level task force, co-chaired by Secretary Wilkie, which will create a comprehensive national public health roadmap to improve the quality of life for veterans and combat the suicide crisis. The task force will focus on developing a national research strategy, investing in research and scientific advances, and working with Congress to provide resources and assistance to empower veterans with critical information and support networks. The President also highlighted the importance of community collaboration and partnership in preventing veteran suicide and emphasized the need for a holistic approach to address the mental health needs of veterans.